---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const S = {
  bg: "#1a1714",
  text: "#f0ece4",
  textDim: "rgba(240,236,228,0.65)",
  textGhost: "rgba(240,236,228,0.4)",
  rule: "rgba(240,236,228,0.12)",
  buttonBorder: "rgba(240,236,228,0.2)",
  buttonText: "rgba(240,236,228,0.55)",
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Submissions — The B-Side of Everything"
  description="Send something to the archive."
  ogImage="/og-image.png"
  ogUrl="https://www.thebsideofeverything.com/submissions"
>
  <div style={`background: ${S.bg}; min-height: 100vh;`}>
    <!-- Nav -->
    <nav style={`
      position: fixed; top: 0; left: 0; right: 0; z-index: 1000;
      background: rgba(26,23,20,0.92);
      backdrop-filter: blur(12px); -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
      border-bottom: 1px solid ${S.rule};
      padding: 0 48px;
      display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between;
      height: 72px;
    `}>
      <a href="/" style={`
        background: rgba(240,236,228,0.06); border: 1px solid rgba(240,236,228,0.35); border-radius: 4px;
        font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: 0.06em;
        color: rgba(240,236,228,0.8); padding: 10px 22px; text-decoration: none;
      `}>&larr; Back to Collection</a>
      <span style={`
        font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 18px; font-weight: 400;
        font-style: italic; color: ${S.textGhost};
      `}>The B-Side of Everything</span>
    </nav>

    <!-- Content -->
    <div style="max-width: min(88vw, 800px); margin: 0 auto; padding: 120px 32px 120px;">
      <h1 style={`
        font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 32px; font-weight: 400;
        color: ${S.text}; margin: 0 0 32px; letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      `}>Send Something</h1>

      <div style={`
        font-family: var(--body); font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.85;
        color: ${S.textDim};
      `}>
        <p style="margin: 0 0 20px;">
          If you've got a piece of music writing that nobody else is going to preserve, I'd like to see it. A review from a zine that folded. Liner notes from a pressing that didn't make it past the first run. A transcript of something someone said on air or in a basement or in a forum thread that's about to disappear. An interview with someone who never got interviewed again.
        </p>
        <p style="margin: 0 0 20px;">
          It doesn't need to be long. It doesn't need to be good in any conventional sense. It needs to be the kind of thing that, if you didn't send it to me, would probably end up in a box that someone throws out in fifteen years.
        </p>

        <div style={`height: 1px; background: ${S.rule}; margin: 32px 0;`}></div>

        <p style="margin: 0 0 20px;">
          Send the text, or a scan, or a photo of it. Tell me where you found it and anything you know about the context. If you wrote it yourself, say so. If you don't remember where you found it, that's fine too. Half of what's already in the collection came to me without much explanation and I figured it out later, or I didn't, and it went in anyway.
        </p>
        <p style="margin: 0 0 20px;">
          I'm not looking for press materials, promo copy, or writing about bands that already have an audience. There are plenty of places for that. This is for the rest of it.
        </p>

        <div style={`height: 1px; background: ${S.rule}; margin: 32px 0;`}></div>

        <p style="margin: 0 0 0;">
          <a href="mailto:submissions@thebsideofeverything.com" style={`color: ${S.text}; text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px solid ${S.rule};`}>submissions@thebsideofeverything.com</a>
        </p>

        <div style={`
          font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 14px; color: ${S.textGhost};
          margin-top: 48px; letter-spacing: 0.06em;
        `}>
          Skinsbury
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
